You have to think to win and get some help from your allies. You also learn patience as you have to hold on some fronts while conducting offensive operations on another. On occasion you might have to "remove" an ally from a territory. With some interface improvements I'd give the game 5 stars.

- this now runs without borders on tablets, and the touch control is spot on. The game itself is a Risk variant  but let down by lack of finish. The graphics are too blurry for tablets: a shame, because the look and feel of this game is a strong selling point. There's also a link to an in-app purchase which doesn't work. 5 stars when fixed.
